            <img class='images' src="https://previews.123rf.com/images/chotwitnote/chotwitnote1711/chotwitnote171100707/91375017-a-vector-set-of-badminton-equipment.jpg" alt="images">
        </p>
        <p class="from-left sliders layout" style="background-color: white; color: black">
            <span>Equipment</span> There is not a lot of equipment needed for badminton. Basic equipment is a racquet, shuttlecock, badminton shoes. Also, of course, an indoor court. The net of the court is about 5 feet (1.5 meters) and stretches across
            the center of the court.
        </p>
    </div>
    <!--content4-->
    <div class="grid">
        <p class="from-left sliders layout" style="background-color: white; color: black">
            <span>Rules</span> No players are allowed to touch the net with their body or their racquet at any time. The shuttlecock should not hit the floor. The shuttlecock should not come to rest on any player’s racket at any time. The shuttlecock
            should not land outside the boundary lines of the court. The shuttlecock should not hit the ceiling. When serving, the shuttlecock should be hit from below the waist. The team receiving the service should not touch the lines on the court before
            the server has hit the shuttlecock.
        </p>
        <p class="from-left sliders title" style="background-color: rgb(22, 97, 82);">
            <br>
            <img class='images' src="https://open.online.uga.edu/app/uploads/sites/20/2018/05/Singles-and-Doubles-Badminton.png" alt="images">
        </p>
    </div>
    <!--content5-->
