        </p>
        <p class="from-left sliders layout" style="background-color: white; color: black">
            <span>How to Win</span> A point is scored when the shuttlecock hits the floor on the opponent’s side regardless of who is serving. The first team to reach 21 points wins the game. However, the winning team must win by two points. In the case
            of a tie at 20 points, the first team to score two additional points is the winner. The first team to reach 30 points is the winner, no matter what the other team has scored. First team to win two out of three games wins the match.
        </p>
